\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering class metadata requirements**\\\\n\\\\nI'm pondering if the argument string from `Class.getName().replace` should be a constant. Inside the library, it’s more dynamic, and I wonder if the native image might include test classes since they can be referenced with class literals in constants. Using class literals can help with naming and assertions, making classes reachable. Even without metadata, `Class.forName` may still require reflection metadata for a native image. Tracking this seems essential.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_AvjKksiwTVkiBaryVKl6ZTGR|fc_07083aa4e0d3106d0169ef6f7ba8a8819689e67434d8ea391c\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/src/test/java/asm/asm/ClassWriterTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.LinkedList;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import java.util.AbstractList;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.LinkedList;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \\\"asm/asm/generated/MergedCollections\\\";\\n    private static final String ARRAY_LIST_NAME = ArrayList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\\n    private static final String LINKED_LIST_NAME = LinkedList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\\n    private static final String ABSTRACT_LIST_NAME = \\\"java/util/AbstractList\\\";\\n\", \"newText\": \"    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \\\"asm/asm/ClassWriterGeneratedMergedLists\\\";\\n    private static final String FIRST_LIST_NAME = ClassWriterTestFirstList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\\n    private static final String SECOND_LIST_NAME = ClassWriterTestSecondList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\\n    private static final String ABSTRACT_LIST_NAME = AbstractList.class.getName().replace('.', '/');\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        String commonSuperClass = classWriter.commonSuperClass(ARRAY_LIST_NAME, LINKED_LIST_NAME);\\n\", \"newText\": \"        Str